.TH CHADDR 1 "June 2026" "chaddr @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
chaddr \- change or reallocate profile-managed IP addresses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B chaddr
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPROFILE\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B chaddr
reads one or more profile files and coordinates updates across cloud APIs,
DNS/name servers, local
.BR hosts (5),
and BIND zone files. Without CLI action flags it opens a graphical editor.
.PP
Profiles live in
.I ~/.config/chaddr/profile
by default. Override with the
.B CHADDR_PROFILE_DIR
environment variable. Example profiles ship in
.I /usr/share/chaddr/profile
when installed from a package, or in
.I profile/
in a source checkout. On first run, an empty user profile directory is seeded
from those examples. Each profile lists resource blocks such as AWS Elastic IP,
Namecheap registered nameservers, hosts files, and BIND db files.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fIFILE\fR
JSON configuration file with API keys and secrets. If omitted,
.B chaddr
searches for
.I ./chaddr.conf
and
.I ~/.config/chaddr/chaddr.conf.
.TP
.B \-\-proxy \fIURL\fR
HTTP or SOCKS proxy URL, for example
.IR socks5://127.0.0.1:1080 .
.TP
.B \-\-diagnose
Run diagnosis only and print results to stdout (CLI mode).
.TP
.B \-\-renew
Reallocate elastic IP addresses and propagate changes (CLI mode).
.TP
.B \-\-apply \fIIP\fR
Apply a new IPv4 or IPv6 address manually (CLI mode). Equivalent to
.B \-\-apply-ipv4
when the value is IPv4.
.TP
.B \-\-apply-ipv4 \fIIP\fR
New IPv4 address for manual apply.
.TP
.B \-\-apply-ipv6 \fIIP\fR
New IPv6 address for manual apply.
.TP
.B \-\-old-ip \fIIP\fR
Old IP to match when automatic detection fails during manual apply or diagnose.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase logging verbosity. Repeat for debug output.
.TP
.B \-\-no-gui
Force CLI mode even when no action flag is given.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is JSON. Copy
.I chaddr.conf.template
to
.I chaddr.conf
and fill in credentials. Keys include AWS, Aliyun, and Namecheap API settings,
optional
.B proxy,
and
.B client_ip
with a one-hour cache expiry when auto-detected.
.PP
Set
.B namecheap_whitelist
to
.I disabled
(the default) to skip portal-based IP whitelisting. Set it to
.I portal
to retry through the Namecheap web UI when API calls fail because the client IP
is not whitelisted.
.SH PROFILES
Each profile file contains blocks such as:
.PP
.RS
.nf
description: Example relay
addr-history: 198.51.100.4 2001:db8::1

from: resolve
resolve: example.example.com

type: aws elastic ip
region: us-east-1

type: registered nameserver
api: namecheap
ns: ns1.example.com, ns2.example.com

type: hosts file
path: /etc/hosts

type: zone file
path: /var/cache/bind/db.example.com
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B from: resolve
with a hostname to discover current addresses. See
.BR chaddr-profile (5)
for the full profile syntax, header fields, resource types, and examples. A
trailing
.B \\
continues a line on the next physical line. Spare addresses from earlier
handlers or the GUI help match old IPs in hosts files.
.SH GUI
The graphical interface lets you select profiles, edit current and new
addresses, diagnose resources, renew elastic IPs, and apply manual changes.
The profile list title shows the active directory, for example
.IR "Profile: ~/.config/chaddr/profile/" .
Use
.B File \(-> Browse...
to switch directories. Use
.B View \(-> Right Pane
(\fBCtrl+H\fR) to show logging and diagnostics tabs.
.PP
Writing protected files such as
.I /etc/hosts
may prompt for elevation through
.BR pkexec (1),
.BR gksudo (1),
or
.BR kdesudo (1).
.SH EXAMPLES
Diagnose a profile:
.PP
.RS
.B chaddr \-\-diagnose \-v example
.RE
.PP
Apply a new IPv4 manually:
.PP
.RS
.B chaddr \-\-apply 203.0.113.10 \-\-old-ip 198.51.100.4 example
.RE
.PP
Launch the GUI with profiles pre-selected:
.PP
.RS
.B chaddr example
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CHADDR_PROFILE_DIR
Directory containing profile files. Default:
.I ~/.config/chaddr/profile/
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/chaddr/profile/
Default profile directory.
.TP
.I ~/.config/chaddr/chaddr.conf
User configuration file.
.TP
.I ./chaddr.conf
Local configuration file in the current directory.
.TP
.I /usr/share/chaddr/profile/
Example profiles installed with the Debian package.
.TP
.I /usr/bin/chaddr
Installed command when built as a Debian package.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR chaddr-profile (5),
.BR hosts (5),
.BR named (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Lenik &lt;chaddr@bodz.net&gt;
